- 6628 - Dashboard performance improvements on instances with many environments and lifecycles

  - 6638 - Infrastructure overview performance improvements on instances with many environments, tenants and/or tags.

WorkItems.Description: Dashboard performance improvements on instances with many environments and lifecycles
Infrastructure overview performance improvements on instances with many environments, tenants and/or tags.

Commits.Comment:
Merge pull request #7448 from OctopusDeploy/john/perf-summary

Avoid iterating multiple times over the data structure for environment summary
Fixes https://github.com/OctopusDeploy/Issues/issues/6638
A few small tweaks based on feedback

Remove zero entries for environment tenant summaries

Reduces the response size by a lot

Avoid iterating multiple times over the data structures

Move all calculations to the ctor so other calls are just look-ups
Fix NextRuntimeCalculatorFixture: would fail if the local time wasn't GMT+10 (#7466)

Merge pull request #7439 from OctopusDeploy/john/perf-honey

Dashboard performance improvements based on large customer database analysis
Fixes https://github.com/OctopusDeploy/Issues/issues/6628

Merge pull request #7454 from OctopusDeploy/rob/perf-honey

Optimised the `GetEnvironmentIds` call

Revert "Azure code signing backport (#7307)"

This reverts commit 371a9a8f7babc3501abc8e482fba02d4ea535e8d.

Reverting, as this approach requires dotnet on the docker build agents.
Instead, we're just going to wait a few months until 2020.3 goes EOL, and decom the DC after that.

Azure code signing backport (#7307)

Changed to use Azure Key Vault for signing instead of storing the certificate on the domain controller.

Use InterceptWith from HashSet

Match equality comparer so intersect works correctly
